description: Several prominent Telugu film industry figures met with Telangana chief minister A Revanth Reddy to resolve issues around the Pusha-2 stampede. The CM pledged full support for developing Hyderabad into an international film hub but emphasized strict law enforcement. He announced a future conclave to promote the industry while reiterating that benefit shows would be prohibited.
title: No law & order compromise: Revanth to Telugu film stars

description: Tamil Nadu BJP president K Annamalai vows not to wear footwear until the DMK government is ousted and plans to publicly flog himself to protest the police's handling of the Anna University rape case. He accuses the police of revealing the survivor's identity and questions the absence of safety measures on campus.
title: Slugfest over Tamil Nadu rape intensifies as BJP neta vows to walk barefoot till DMK government ousted

description: Women had a higher turnout than men in the 2024 Lok Sabha election, with 65.8% participating compared to men's 65.6%. Despite increased female voter participation, only 9.5% of the total candidates were women, with 74 elected. The electorate grew to nearly 98 crore, with 64.6 crore casting votes, 66.1% turnout recorded overall.
title: Women voters clocked 65.8%, men 65.6% in '24 Lok Sabha polls: Election Commission

description: RJD MLA Bhai Birendra indicated that Bihar CM Nitish Kumar would be welcomed if he left the BJP alliance, emphasizing the fluid nature of political alliances. His remarks hinted at possible political shifts, while JD(U) and BJP dismissed them as attempts to create confusion following RJD’s recent electoral setbacks.
title: Will welcome back Nitish Kumar if he ditches BJP, says Lalu aide

description: BJP criticizes Congress for displaying a distorted map of India at an event in Karnataka's Belagavi, showing Kashmir as part of Pakistan. They accuse Congress of engaging in appeasement politics and suggest potential foreign influence in this action, specifically mentioning billionaire investor George Soros.
title: BJP attacks Congress for displaying 'distorted' Indian map at meet

description: Rohit Sharma faces a crucial juncture in his cricket career, with the Melbourne Test possibly determining his future as India's Test captain. Former England spinner Monty Panesar asserts that these four innings could either save Rohit's career or lead to his retirement, amid a string of poor performances and India facing intense competition from Australia.
title: 'Rohit has four innings to save his Test career': Panesar

description: Milwaukee Bucks' star Giannis Antetokounmpo is questionable for the Thursday game against the Brooklyn Nets due to back spasms. Despite his absence, the Bucks have managed recent wins, improving their standing to fifth in the Eastern Conference. Antetokounmpo leads the NBA in scoring and rebounds, making his recovery crucial for the team's success.
title: Will Giannis Antetokounmpo play against the Brooklyn Nets tonight? Latest update on the Milwaukee Bucks star's injury update (December 26, 2024)

description: Union consumer affairs minister Pralhad Joshi has ordered a detailed investigation by the Central Consumer Protection Authority into the disparity in cab fares on Android and IOS devices reported by TOI. The inquiry will also extend to other sectors such as food delivery apps and online ticket booking platforms.
title: After TOI report, Centre orders probe into differential pricing by ride-hailing apps

description: The Calcutta High Court ruled on Dec 19 that allegations of cruelty in divorce cases must be supported by concrete evidence. The decision came as the court dismissed a man's plea for divorce based on claims of cruelty and desertion, stating that the petitioner failed to substantiate his allegations with any substantial proof.
title: Cruelty charges need some proof in divorce cases: High court

description: At a meeting to counter criticism on the BR Ambedkar issue, NDA leaders, including home minister Amit Shah and BJP president J P Nadda, resolved to present a united front. Shah claimed his statements were misrepresented to create unrest, while Congress allegedly conspired to highlight the remarks for political gain. The discussion occurred on Vajpayee's birth centenary.
title: NDA to put up united front to take on opposition over Ambedkar

description: The Karnataka High Court has annulled legal action against two individuals who endorsed PM Modi on a wedding card. The judge deemed the investigation and chargesheet as reckless. The bridegroom and the printing press owner had been accused under section 188 of the IPC and section 127A of the Representation of People Act.
title: 'Reckless probe': High court quashes case over 'pro-Modi' wedding invite

description: Six months post BJD's electoral defeat in Odisha, Naveen Patnaik cited the party's failure to counter BJP's false narratives as the main reason. On BJD's 28th foundation day, Patnaik emphasized that misleading BJP campaigns led to their loss, shifting focus away from aide VK Pandian's role.
title: Naveen Patnaik spares VK Pandian, links loss to BJP's 'bundle of lies'

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi launched the Suposhit Gram Panchayat Abhiyan on Veer Bal Diwas, commemorating the martyrdom of Guru Gobind Singh’s sons. The campaign aims to promote healthy living and combat malnutrition.
title: PM Modi launches drive to combat malnutrition on Veer Bal Diwas

description: The Karnataka high court has ruled that the registrar of births and deaths must change gender details on birth or death certificates if appropriate transgender certificates are presented.
title: Tweak birth & death papers if transgender certificate given: High court

description: RSS-affiliated magazine 'The Organiser' emphasized the call for restoring temples now housing mosques as a matter of national identity and civilizational justice. The editorial advocates a truthful historical debate, following Ambedkar's views on past invasions and temple destruction. This contrasts with RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat's recent call to avoid new, divisive issues.
title: Temple restoration claims a quest for justice: RSS weekly

description: The Vishva Hindu Parishad announced a nationwide campaign to free temples from government control, citing discriminatory practices against Hindus. Organising general secretary Milind Parande noted thousands of temples are under government oversight in 11 states. The campaign, starting January 5, includes proposals for autonomous management by Hindu councils, emphasizing decentralized control for better religious and social service.
title: VHP launches nationwide campaign to 'free' temples from government control

description: Tensions rise in Sambhal following clashes over claims that the Shahi Jama Masjid was built over a demolished Hindu temple. The district administration's excavation efforts and anti-encroachment drives, including actions against Samajwadi Party MP Zia Ur Rehman Barq, have exacerbated fears among locals. The UP government is focusing on restoring and protecting Hindu temples in the area.
title: 'They're excavating everywhere': In Sambhal, a mammoth 'facelift'

description: In 2023-24, banks experienced the lowest fraud amounts in a decade and the least average fraud amount in 16 years. However, in the first half of FY25, the fraud amount surged to Rs 21,397 crore with internet and card frauds comprising a significant share.
title: Bank frauds jump 8 times in first half of FY25 over a year
Pak military court sentence 60 more civilians, including Imran’s nephew, to jail terms

description: The finance ministry's report indicates that the combination of RBI's monetary policy and structural factors may have led to the economic slowdown. The ministry highlighted slowed urban consumption and cautious corporate hiring practices as contributors. The report anticipates improved growth in the second half of FY25, while stressing the need for a comprehensive commitment to sustaining growth amidst global uncertainties.
title: RBI policies may have contributed to economic slowdown: Finance ministry

description: The Union government declared a seven-day national mourning for former Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, who passed away at 92. His last rites will be conducted with full state honours. Congress has cancelled all official programs for seven days in his respect. The Union cabinet will meet to pay tribute to the veteran leader.
title: Manmohan Singh's demise: Govt declares 7-day national mourning

description: Former Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, who led India from 2004 to 2014, will be remembered for his pivotal role in transforming India's economy. Under his leadership, India achieved an average growth rate of 7.7%, becoming a nearly two trillion-dollar economy. His tenure was marked by significant economic policies and rights-based governance, empowering millions and elevating India's global economic status.
title: Manmohan Singh, visionary reformer who shaped modern India

description: Former Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, aged 92, passed away in New Delhi. He was admitted to AIIMS hospital and is recognised for being a key architect of India's economic reforms during his tenure as finance minister (1991-1996). Tributes from leaders highlight his significant contributions to the nation's governance.
title: Former PM and Congress veteran Manmohan Singh passes away at 92

description: Virat Kohli faced criticism and a fine after a shoulder bump with Sam Konstas during the Boxing Day Test. Kohli was fined 20% of his match fees and given a demerit point for inappropriate physical contact. The incident, reminiscent of a 2018 clash between Kagiso Rabada and Steve Smith, highlights the ongoing scrutiny of player conduct on the cricket field.
title: Kohli-Konstas shoulder bump evokes memories of Rabada-Smith clash

description: Former Pakistani cricketer Basit Ali condemns Virat Kohli's physical altercation with Australian debutant Sam Konstas during the fourth Test at the MCG. Basit criticizes Kohli for intentionally colliding with Konstas, contrasting his behavior with Sachin Tendulkar's. The ICC fines Kohli with a 20% match fee and a demerit point, raising debates on disciplinary consistency.
title: 'Tendulkar always answered with bat': Basit slams Kohli

description: Former Prime Minister Manmohan Singh passed away at 92 due to age-related conditions.  Singh, who retired from Rajya Sabha after 33 years, is remembered for his pivotal role in India's economic reforms. Known for his integrity, he expressed confidence that history would treat him kindly despite criticism during his tenure.
title: 'I feel I have done reasonably well': Top quotes of former PM Manmohan Singh

description: Mani Shankar Aiyar reveals in his book how Dr. Manmohan Singh, after undergoing multiple coronary bypasses in 2012, never fully recovered, affecting his governance. Aiyar suggests that Pranab Mukherjee should have taken over as PM, with Singh elevated to President in 2012. Singh's key achievements include MGNREGA, RTI Act, and National Food Security Act.
title: In 2012, Manmohan underwent operations, never quite recovered physically

description: Manmohan Singh, ex-Prime Minister and veteran Congress leader, passed away at 92 in Delhi. Singh, known for his central role in India's economic reforms, served as Prime Minister from 2004 to 2014. He also held significant positions like Governor of the Reserve Bank and Chief Economic Adviser, leaving behind a legacy of economic transformation.
title: 1991 reforms that reshaped India: Highlights from Manmohan Singh's career
Manmohan Singh lost consciousness at home: AIIMS statement
'An extraordinarily distinguished life': Tributes pour in for Manmohan Singh

description: Former Indian Prime Minister Manmohan Singh passed away at 92. Singh, who served as PM from 2004 to 2014, made significant contributions like the Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Act, Right to Information Act, and National Food Security Act. A distinguished economist, Singh's legacy includes roles as Finance Minister and receiving the Padma Vibhushan in 1987.
title: Manmohan Singh, architect of India's economic reforms, bids farewell at 92

description: Batting maestro Virat Kohli avoided a ban after a shoulder bump with Australian debutant Sam Konstas during the fourth Test in Melbourne. The ICC fined Kohli 20% of his match fee and awarded a demerit point. The altercation, deemed a Level 1 or 2 offence, sparked debate on disciplinary consistency, with Kohli accepting his sanction.
title: Why Kohli was not handed a ban despite shoulder-bumping Konstas

description: A fierce skirmish has emerged in Trumpworld between his 'tech cabal' and MAGA nativists over the appointment of Indian-American Sriram Krishnan as the White House AI policy advisor. Trump loyalist Laura Loomer and others criticized the pick, citing concerns about foreign influence, while Musk and other tech leaders defended Krishnan, emphasizing the need for skilled immigration.
title: Racist rants, resentment against Indians in US after MAGA meltdown over Trump's AI pick

description: Travis Kelce has upgraded the security of his $6 million mansion in Kansas City for his girlfriend, Taylor Swift, following a recent burglary. He installed a safety room and hired round-the-clock security. Taylor, focusing on their safety, has been cautious this NFL season, only attending home games at the Arrowhead Stadium due to its secure environment.
title: Travis Kelce’s $6mn mansion undergoes major security upgrades

description: Sebastian Zapeta-Calil, a Guatemalan migrant with a history of erratic behavior due to substance abuse, has been charged with first-degree murder and arson for setting a woman on fire while she slept on a Brooklyn subway train. His roommates describe him as a heavy K2 and alcohol user, with altered but non-violent behavior when sober.
title: NYC subway murder suspect used to behave erratically after smoking 'K2' drug

description: The Supreme Court has ruled that banks can legally charge interest rates exceeding 30% on credit card dues, overriding a previous NCDRC decision. The ruling states that the NCDRC lacked authority to alter mutually agreed contractual terms and emphasized that credit card holders are informed and aware of their payment obligations and potential penalties.
title: SC allows banks to charge 30% interest rates on credit card dues
Former PM Manmohan Singh admitted to AIIMS: Report

description: The Kazakhstan plane crash claiming 38 lives has led to speculation involving possible bird strike, adverse weather, or Russian air defense systems. Ukrainian officials and Andriy Kovalenko highlighted evidence of a Russian air defense missile strike. Contrarily, Russia noted factors like bird collision and heavy fog.
title: Bird, weather, or Russia — What really caused the Kazakhstan plane crash?

description: Virat Kohli was fined for inappropriate physical contact after shoulder-barging Australian teenager Sam Konstas during the Boxing Day Test at Melbourne. Kohli, known for his aggressive play, did not take kindly to the 19-year-old's attacking knock. Although some believe suspending him for a first offence would be harsh, it's urged that a repeated behavior should bring a suspension.
title: 'Suspend Kohli if he misbehaves again': Panesar

description: West Bengal chief minister Mamata Banerjee plans to visit Sandeshkhali on December 30 for a public distribution program amidst earlier protests over sexual harassment accusations against local TMC leaders. The visit will focus on state-run schemes like 'Lakshmir Bhandar' and 'Banglar Bari', benefitting around 20,000 residents.
title: Mamata Banerjee to visit Sandeshkhali for first time since protests

description: India may reduce income tax for individuals earning up to Rs 15 lakh annually in the upcoming budget to support the middle class and drive consumption. This potential change, under the 2020 tax system, could alleviate financial pressures on millions and stimulate economic growth, particularly in urban areas struggling with high inflation and living costs.
title: Govt considers income tax relief for those earning up to Rs 15L

description: Elon Musk refuted claims that foreign-born tech workers in the US are taking jobs from qualified Americans, highlighting a persistent shortage of engineering talent in Silicon Valley. This debate coincides with the backlash over Sriram Krishnan's appointment as a White House AI policy advisor, stressing the limitless potential for job creation.
title: Musk to tech CEO on 'foreign-born workers taking jobs from Americans'

description: Tamil Nadu BJP president K Annamalai pledged to boycott footwear until the DMK government is ousted, after the sexual harassment case at Anna University. He announced a personal protest, including self-whipping and fasting, amid ongoing demonstrations led by the BJP and AIADMK accusing the DMK of suppressing dissent.
title: 'Whip 6 times, not wear shoes till ...': Annamalai's dramatic protest against DMK

description: Simran Singh, a prominent social media influencer and radio jockey from Jammu and Kashmir, was found dead by suicide in Gurugram. Her body was discovered hanging in her room, with no suicide note present. The family reported that she faced ongoing difficulties. A post-mortem was conducted, and no case has been filed. Simran had over six lakh Instagram followers.
title: Simran Singh, influencer & RJ from J&K, dies by suicide in Gurugram

description: Bigg Boss 18 is heating up with dramatic incidents, including Avinash Mishra's confrontations and an impending physical altercation between Karan Veer Mehra and Sara Arfeen Khan. Tensions escalate as Vivian Dsena intervenes to resolve the dispute, amidst emotional turmoil and accusations flying in the show.
title: Bigg Boss 18: Karan Veer Mehra dares Vivian Dsena to get him evicted

description: Japan Airlines experienced a cyberattack on December 26, leading to system disruptions and the suspension of ticket sales. The attack caused delays of over 24 domestic flights. No customer data was compromised. Operations were restored later, with flights resuming normally by December 27. Authorities are investigating, and the incident occurred during Japan's peak New Year holiday travel season.
title: Japan Airlines says systems back to normal after cyberattack

description: Ravi Shastri drew parallels between Australia's Sam Konstas and Virender Sehwag after Konstas's 60 off 65 balls against India, praising his fearless stroke play. Shastri noted that despite early setbacks, Konstas has the potential to entertain fans like Sehwag. With Australia at 311/6, the match remains evenly poised with Day 2's action anticipated keenly.
title: Sam Konstas reminds me a lot of Sehwag: Ravi Shastri

description: A significant fire at the Bangladesh Secretariat in Dhaka caused severe damage to critical documents within Building 7 housing seven ministries. Firefighters controlled the blaze after six hours. Authorities suspect sabotage and formed a high-level committee to investigate. Destroyed documents reportedly held evidence of financial misconduct. No casualties were reported.
title: Watch: Fire breaks out at Bangladesh Secretariat, damages documents

description: India's Mohammed Siraj hilariously teased Australia's Marnus Labuschagne by flipping the bails during the Boxing Day Test, leaving commentators amused. The strategy worked as Jasprit Bumrah dismissed Labuschagne soon after, breaking a vital partnership. Australia's top order shone on day one, ending at 311 for six, with fifties from the top-four batters.
title: Marnus, look at that! Siraj's hilarious bail-flip tease. Watch

description: Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge emphasised the need for organizational empowerment and nurturing local leadership. He criticised PM Modi for not addressing Amit Shah's remarks on B R Ambedkar. Kharge also raised concerns about the impartiality of the Election Commission and the involvement of ideologically committed individuals to protect the Constitution. Kharge promised to fully implement the Udaipur Declaration.
title: 'Need to give chance to new power, leadership': Kharge at CWC meet

description: Rahul Gandhi has accused the Election Commission of rigging the recently concluded Maharashtra assembly elections. He cited a substantial increase of 72 lakh voters after the Lok Sabha elections, mainly benefitting the BJP. The Congress expressed concerns about deleted voters and anomalous voter rolls, questioning the legitimacy of the election results.
title: 'Big change in voters' list': Rahul alleges rigging in Maharashtra polls

description: Former India coach Ravi Shastri on Tuesday commended 19-year-old Australian Sam Konstas for his bold batting against Indian pacer Jasprit Bumrah, on his Test debut at the MCG. Konstas scored 60 runs off 65 balls, attacking Bumrah in an impressive over. Australia's top order played crucial roles, reaching 311/6 on the first day.
title: 'Don't think anyone has treated Bumrah like that'

description: Naveen Patnaik, BJD chief, has given a reserved response regarding Union Minister Giriraj Singh's proposal for awarding Bharat Ratna to him and Bihar's Nitish Kumar. Singh praised both leaders' significant contributions to their states. Despite strained relationships between the BJD and BJP, BJD's Amar Patnaik welcomed Singh's statement, acknowledging Naveen Patnaik's dedicated service to Odisha.
title: Naveen Patnaik shrugs off Giriraj Singh's Bharat Ratna proposal

description: Virat Kohli was fined 20% of his match fee and received a demerit point for an altercation with Australian debutant Sam Konstas in the fourth Test in Melbourne. This incident adds to Kohli's history of ICC penalties, including instances in 2019, 2018, 2016, 2014, 2012, and 2010 for various on-field violations.
title: Kohli and ICC penalties: A look at all the instances

description: Rahul Gandhi condemns the Bihar government's lathi charge on BPSC candidates protesting against a paper leak and demanding exam cancellation. He calls the act 'shameful and reprehensible.' Lalu Prasad Yadav also criticizes the police's actions. Despite protesters' claims of injuries, the SSP denies them, stating only mild force was used to disperse the crowd.
title: Watch: Rahul Gandhi shares video of police brutality on protesting BPSC aspirants

description: China has approved the construction of the world's largest dam on the Brahmaputra River in Tibet, near the Indian border. Estimated to cost $137 billion, this project raises concerns in India and Bangladesh about water flow control, regional stability, and potential flooding risks. Advanced geological explorations ensure safety amid seismic activity.
title: China plans largest dam on Brahmaputra: How will it impact India

description: Chaos erupted at a BJP event in Patna when folk singer Devi sang Mahatma Gandhi's version of 'Raghupati Raghav,' leading to protests by some audience members. Ex-Union minister Ashwini Choubey intervened with chants of 'Jai Shree Ram.' Opposition parties, including Congress and RJD, criticized the BJP for allegedly disrespecting Gandhi and women.
title: Politics heats up over 'Raghupati Raghav' bhajan at BJP event in Bihar

description: BJP condemned Congress and Rahul Gandhi for allegedly misrepresenting Indian maps at an event in Karnataka celebrating the 1924 Congress session. BJP accused Congress of disrespecting India's sovereignty and engaging in vote bank politics, while Congress leaders dismissed the criticism, attributing it to jealousy. BJP demands police action against the organizers for violating laws concerning the accurate depiction of the Indian map.
title: BJP vs Congress now over 'incorrect India map'

description: AAP leader Sanjay Singh filed a complaint against BJP's Parvesh Verma for allegedly distributing cash to women ahead of Delhi elections. Arvind Kejriwal and Delhi CM Atishi condemned Verma's actions, calling for his arrest. Verma defended his initiative as financial aid through Rashtriya Swabhiman, contrasting it with Kejriwal's alleged distribution of alcohol.
title: Sanjay Singh files complaint with ED against BJP's Parvesh Verma

description: Virat Kohli and debutant Sam Konstas had a heated exchange after shoulder-bumping during the Boxing Day Test in Melbourne. Former Australian skipper Ricky Ponting criticized Kohli, calling his actions confrontational. Indian fans quickly pointed out Ponting's hypocrisy by sharing a video of a previous incident. Kohli was fined 20% of his match fee and given a demerit point.
title: Shoulder-bump row: Ponting's hypocrisy highlighted
Watch: Moving Lamborghini bursts into flames on busy Mumbai road

description: Virat Kohli has been fined 20 percent of his match fees for a physical altercation with Australian debutant Sam Konstas during Day 1 of the Boxing Day Test. The incident, which involved shoulder contact and heated words, avoided a Level 2 offence, thereby sparing Kohli a potential suspension. Australia finished the day on 311/6.
title: Virat Kohli fined, handed one demerit point for Sam Konstas shoulder barge

description: This year, the UK royals celebrated Christmas at Sandringham without Prince Harry and Meghan. Prince Harry was replaced by Prince George in the traditional pre-Christmas football match, signifying the strained relationship between Harry and his family. Prince George participated alongside Prince William, highlighting healthy father-son bonding moments.
title: Prince Harry no longer invited to this major royal tradition

description: Former cricketers criticized Virat Kohli for bumping into Australian rookie Sam Konstas during the fourth Test in Melbourne. The incident occurred while Konstas was off to a flying start. Umpire Michael Gough and Usman Khawaja intervened to calm the situation. Ravi Shastri and Michael Vaughan disapproved of Kohli's actions, deeming them unnecessary and inappropriate.
title: 'Absolutely unnecessary': Shastri on Kohli's confrontation with Konstas

description: Indian assistant coach Abhishek Nayar clarified that Shubman Gill's exclusion from the fourth Test against Australia was a strategic decision based on pitch conditions. All-rounder Washington Sundar was preferred to add depth and balance to the team. Nayar emphasized it was not a reflection on Gill's form. The decision has sparked discussions among cricket enthusiasts.
title: 'Not really dropped': Nayar on Gill's exclusion from playing XI

description: Symbiosis International University (SIU) has declared the SLAT 2025 results on its official website, slat-test.org. The results are for the exams held on December 13 and 15, 2024. SLAT is SIU’s entrance exam for admissions to its law programs. Candidates can check and download their results online on the official website, or can check the direct link here.
title: SLAT 2025 result declared, check direct link here

description: Indian chess prodigy D Gukesh, the youngest World Chess Champion, will miss the 2024 World Rapid and Blitz Championships in New York for rest and recovery. Gukesh's decision follows his intense 14-game win over Ding Liren. India's hopes now rest on rising stars Praggnanandhaa and Arjun Erigaisi, while Magnus Carlsen remains the favorite.
title: Why Gukesh will not play in World Rapid and Blitz Championships

description: Sam Konstas made a memorable Test debut with a brilliant 60 off 65 balls against India, boldly taking on Jasprit Bumrah. His brother Billy revealed a childhood error by their father exposed Sam to high-speed bowling early on. Australia's aggressive approach led them to 311 for six on the first day, with the Konstas family feeling both nervous and blessed.
title: How facing Jasprit Bumrah came naturally to Sam Konstas

description: Indian captain Rohit Sharma is set to return to his opening role in the fourth Test against Australia, with KL Rahul moving to No.3 and Shubman Gill being excluded for this match. Australia's top-order, led by teenage opener Sam Konstas' explosive 60, took command on day one, finishing at 311/6 at the MCG.
title: Rohit's batting slot all but confirmed for Boxing Day Test

description: An old video of young Australian cricketer Sam Konstas expressing admiration for Virat Kohli has gone viral. This resurfaced clip coincided with an on-field altercation between Konstas and Kohli during the opening day of the Boxing Day Test at MCG. Konstas downplayed the incident, calling it an accidental bump and part of cricket’s high tensions.
title: Konstas’ old fanboy moment for Kohli goes viral. Watch

description: Opener Sam Konstas made a memorable Test debut, scoring an impressive 65-ball 60 against India on the first day of the Melbourne Test. Konstas aggressively took on bowler Jasprit Bumrah, hitting him for 18 runs in one over. Australia ended Day 1 at 311 for six, with the series tied at 1-1 after three Tests.
title: Kaboom! 19-year-old forces Bumrah to an unwanted record

description: Australian opener Sam Konstas had a memorable debut against India in the Boxing Day Test at the MCG, marked by an impressive 60 off 65 balls and an on-field altercation with Virat Kohli. Despite the emotional exchange, Konstas later revealed that Kohli is his favorite player.
title: Watch: When Sam Konstas chose Virat Kohli over Steve Smith

description: YouTuber Ranveer Allahbadia, also known as BeerBiceps, and his girlfriend were rescued from drowning in Goa after getting caught in a strong underwater current. Despite being strong swimmers, they struggled and were helped to safety by an IPS officer and his IRS wife. The experience left them grateful for life and with a changed perspective.
title: YouTuber Ranveer Allahbadia, gf rescued from drowning by IPS officer

description: On the first day of the Melbourne Test, Virat Kohli and Sam Konstas had a brief confrontation after an accidental shoulder bump. The incident was quickly intervened by Usman Khawaja and umpires. Konstas confirmed it was accidental and scored a remarkable fifty in his debut match against India.
title: Virat Kohli accidently bumped into me: Sam Konstas

description: A 21-year-old electrician, Asgar Ali, committed suicide while on a video call with his girlfriend in Deoria, UP. They had been in a relationship for over a year and wanted to marry, but her family opposed. After a lengthy conversation and argument, Asgar made the drastic decision to end his life. Police are investigating the incident.
title: UP man ends life while on video call with girlfriend

description: A Zomato delivery agent was pressured by right-wing activists to remove his Santa Claus costume in Indore, citing it goes against their culture. The agent stated he wore it as part of Zomato's Christmas drive. Zomato confirmed the costume distribution but has not commented on the viral video.
title: ‘Do you dress as Lord Ram?’: Zomato delivery agent forced to remove Santa costume

description: Aam Admi Party (AAP) criticized Congress, accusing it of collaborating with BJP ahead of the Delhi elections. AAP leader Sanjay Singh demanded action against Congress leader Ajay Maken for his derogatory remarks about Arvind Kejriwal. AAP warned of potential withdrawal from the INDIA bloc if Congress's actions do not align with their principles.
title: 'Will ask INDIA bloc parties to remove Congress from alliance,' says AAP

description: On the first day of the fourth Test of the Border-Gavaskar Trophy, Indian captain Rohit Sharma confronted Australian batter Marnus Labuschagne over running on the pitch. The incident led to a long exchange, with Labuschagne eventually agreeing. Washington Sundar later dismissed Labuschagne for 72 runs, setting the stage for an intense battle.
title: Watch: Rohit Sharma confronts Labuschagne over pitch running

description: Australia ended the opening day of the fourth Test with 311 for six, thanks to half-centuries from Sam Konstas, Usman Khawaja, Marnus Labuschagne, and Steve Smith. Debutant Konstas impressed with 60 off 65 balls, sparking high drama with Virat Kohli. Jasprit Bumrah fought back with three wickets, leaving the contest open on day two.
title: 4th Test: Konstas, top-order put Aus on top despite Bumrah's late strikes

description: Telangana CM Revanth Reddy met with Tollywood representatives to reinforce public safety measures, following the tragic incident at Allu Arjun's film premiere. Emphasizing zero compromise on law and order, he urged the film industry to act responsibly and control their fans. The meeting aimed at addressing the tensions between the state government and Tollywood.
title: Pushpa stampede row: 'Celebrities must be responsible', CM tells Telugu stars

description: Amid the controversy over the stampede during Pushpa2's premiere, the action drama's earnings of around Rs 1,500 crore contrast starkly with the Andhra Pradesh government's struggles to sell red sanders. Despite permission to auction 11,000 tonnes, no red sandalwood has been sold internationally since the pandemic, with even China showing little interest due to economic slowdown.
title: Pushpa rakes in Rs 1,500 crore, but Andhra's red sanders find no buyers

description: Michael Dell, CEO of Dell Technologies, advises young techies to take bold risks and forge their own paths, acknowledging that while parental advice can be right or wrong, it's important to experiment and find balance. Dell emphasizes a fun workplace culture and a disciplined lifestyle, crediting his mother’s mantra, 'play nice but win,' as influential.
title: Dell CEO to young techies: Your parents aren't always right, but ...

description: The fourth Border-Gavaskar Trophy Test at the Melbourne Cricket Ground saw intense competition. Australia's debutant Sam Konstas scored 60 off 65. Rohit Sharma scolded fielder Yashasvi Jaiswal for premature play. By tea, Australia was at 176/2. Both teams are fighting for a crucial win in the series, tied at 1-1.
title: 'Gully cricket khel raha hai kya?': Captain Rohit rebukes Yashasvi Jaiswal

description: Sam Konstas made an impressive Test debut for Australia at the Melbourne Cricket Ground, bravely facing Jasprit Bumrah and hitting two sixes. His daring approach and 60-run innings rattled India, leading to on-field exchange with Virat Kohli. Konstas's performance provided Australia with an early advantage, living up to the iconic fixture's expectations.
title: How a 19-year-old Sam Konstas riled up Virat Kohli, Team India

description: A husband's plea in Gujarat high court for custody of his pregnant wife was dismissed after she chose to stay with her lesbian friend. The woman cited mental and physical harassment and was set free to live as she wished. She denied illegal confinement, affirming her voluntary departure from her matrimonial home.
title: Gujarat man moves court as wife picks female friend over him

description: In Rohtak, a Christmas event turned chaotic when Vishwa Hindu Parishad and Bajrang Dal members disrupted, accusing organizers of using the celebration for religious conversion. The protestors recited 'Hanuman Chalisa' on stage. WWE wrestler 'The Great Khali' left without attending. The organizers denied the conversion allegation, stating the event aimed at spreading hope.
title: VHP, Bajrang Dal protest at Christmans event in Haryana, recite Hanuman Chalisa

description: The district administration and Municipal Corporation in Sambhal have commenced the revival of 68 pilgrimage sites and 19 ancient wells, including the Mrityu Koop. Excavation of the encroached well started near the Jama mosque, with efforts aimed at restoring ancient heritage linked to Sambhal's historical significance.
title: Sambhal revives ancient 'Mrityu Koop' well near Jama masjid

description: An Australia-based NRI businessman was defrauded by a taxi driver at Mumbai airport. The driver charged Rs 2,800 for a 10-minute ride to Vile Parle using a fake app. The cheating was detected after the businessman reached his hotel. The taxi driver was later arrested by the police following a complaint from the victim.
title: Mumbai cabbie charges NRI Rs 2,800 for 10-minute ride with fake app, held

description: South Africa's strong performance has placed them as the front-runners for the World Test Championship Final, while Australia and India are in a close contest for the remaining spot. Sri Lanka's chances are slim but not entirely extinguished. The fourth Test is underway between India and Australia at the Melbourne Cricket Ground.
title: WTC Standings: How the points table could change after Boxing Day Test

description: Pune DCP Sandeep Bhajibhakre saved a critically injured boy by swiftly administering first aid after a car accident at Jagtap Chowk. His prompt response and medical expertise prevented a tragic outcome, earning widespread praise. Bhajibhakre's actions highlight the importance of timely intervention and calmness during emergencies to ensure victims' safety.
title: Pune DCP's timely action saves the life of an accident-hit man

description: IRCTC's website and mobile app experienced a significant outage on Thursday morning, disrupting Tatkal ticket bookings during the critical 10 AM window. Users faced maintenance errors and reported only premium-priced tickets available once the service resumed. The issue drew criticism and calls for an investigation into the platform's server capacity and transparency.
title: IRCTC down: Users not able to book tatkal tickets on app and website
Dead body found in wheel well of United flight from Chicago to Hawaii

description: YouTuber Ranveer Allahbadia, also known as BeerBiceps, shared that he and his girlfriend were rescued by an IPS officer and his IRS wife while nearly drowning in Goa. Both were caught by an underwater current but were saved by a nearby family. The experience left them deeply grateful and reflective.
title: ‘Started fading away’: 'BeerBiceps' recounts drowning scare with girlfriend in Goa

description: Elon Musk shared a photo dressed as Santa Claus, engaging social media users. He compared this look with a childhood Santa photo, receiving praise and humorous comments. The posts, shared on X, also saw AI-generated images of Musk and some users discussing the Ozempic reference.
title: ‘Ozempic Santa’: Elon Musk shares quirky picture of himself on Christmas Day
Luigi Mangione's courtroom sweater sells out as fans rush to copy his look
Bashar-al Assad’s wife Asma battling leukemia, '50/50' chance of survival: Report

description: The planetary outlook for Moon signs in 2025 predicts social, financial, and health prospects. Aries and Leo will experience significant career growth, while Taurus enjoys stable finances. Other signs face challenges in relationships, health, or legal issues, mitigated by strategic planning and preventive measures. Women's roles across signs see balanced growth.
title: Lunar horoscopes 2025: Discover what your Moon sign says about the future

description: Jasprit Bumrah provided a crucial breakthrough for India on the first day of the fourth Test against Australia by dismissing Usman Khawaja for 57. Australia's strong start was led by debutant Sam Konstas' quickfire 60, with Khawaja and Labuschagne adding 65 for the second wicket. Bumrah's timely wicket left Australia at 154 for 2.
title: Five times in six innings! Bumrah gets the better of Khawaja

description: During a farewell party for Devendra Sandal, a manager at the central warehouse in Kota, his wife Deepika, who had cardiac issues, suddenly collapsed and was declared dead at the hospital. The couple had no children, and Sandal had taken early retirement to care for his ailing wife.
title: Man takes early retirement to take care of wife, she dies on farewell party

description: Vishal Gawli, with prior cases of sexual assault, was arrested for the rape and murder of a 13-year-old girl in Kalyan. After the crime, he and his wife, Sakshi, transported the body in an autorickshaw to Bhiwandi and dumped it. CCTV footage helped in tracking them down, leading to Sakshi's confession and Gawli's capture.
title: Kalyan girl rape-murder suspect held while trying to change look

description: Sam Konstas, a 19-year-old debutant, captivated the Melbourne Cricket Ground with a remarkable half-century against India. His aggressive play and fearless exchanges, including a memorable run-in with Virat Kohli, caught fans' attention. His performance led to viral Wikipedia edits, showcasing his impact on the game and generating significant social media buzz.
title: 'Father of ...': Konstas' Wiki page gets doctored after MCG exploits

description: Australia's rivalry with India intensified when Virat Kohli collided with 19-year-old batter Sam Konstas during the fourth test at Melbourne. The incident sparked a heated exchange until Usman Khawaja intervened. Australia, who went into lunch at 112-1, saw Konstas score a memorable 60 on debut. Both teams made changes as they seek to secure a series lead.
title: What did Konstas say on the Kohli shoulder-bump?

description: During the Boxing Day Test at the Melbourne Cricket Ground, Virat Kohli sparked controversy by shoulder-bumping debutant Sam Konstas, leading to a heated exchange. Konstas, who eventually scored a half-century, was instrumental for Australia after Pat Cummins won the toss. Ricky Ponting criticized Kohli's actions, suggesting potential consequences from umpires and referees.
title: Ricky Ponting slams Virat Kohli for Sam Konstas confrontation

description: India's Virat Kohli showed his animated side on the first day of the Boxing Day Test against Australia, instructing Mohammad Siraj and making a shoulder bump with debutant Sam Konstas. Skipper Rohit Sharma also gave crucial guidance to spinner Ravindra Jadeja. Australia's strong start, led by Konstas' 60, put them at 112 for 1 at lunch.
title: 'Has ke baat nahi karna inse': Kohli's fiery instructions to Siraj

description: The Akhil Bharatiya Akhada Parishad dismisses threats by Khalistani terrorist Gurpatwant Singh Pannun against the Maha Kumbh, calling them attempts to sow discord between Hindus and Sikhs. President Mahant Ravindra Puri assures unity, highlights Sikh contributions to Sanatan Dharma, and downplays the threats as routine disruptions.
title: 'Seen hundreds of lunatics': Religious body brushes off Pannun’s Maha Kumbh threat

description: A thin layer of fog covered parts of Delhi this morning, lowering the temperature to 7°C. Dense fog has disrupted rail services but flight operations remain unaffected. The IMD has issued a yellow alert, forecasting moderate to dense fog and possible light rainfall. Supreme Court guidelines on air quality management may impose restrictions based on AQI.
title: Dense fog envelops Delhi as IMD issues yellow alert; train ops affected

description: Former cricketer Sanjay Manjrekar criticised India's decision to drop batsman Shubman Gill for the Boxing Day Test against Australia. He called the move harsh and noted it did not significantly improve either the batting or bowling performance. The series is tied at 1-1, with crucial matches ahead. The series is currently tied at 1-1, with both teams vying for an important series lead in the Boxing Day Test as they aim for a spot in the ICC World Test Championship final.
title: 'Dropping Shubman Gill is harsh': Manjrekar slams Team India

description: Japan Airlines experienced a cyberattack causing disruptions to both internal and external systems, impacting domestic and international flights. Travelers were advised to stay updated and allocate extra time at airports. This incident follows a similar cyberattack earlier this year at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport, highlighting the increasing vulnerability of critical infrastructure.
title: Japan airlines hit by cyberattack, flights affected: All you need to know

description: David Sacks defends Sriram Krishnan, Trump's nominee for AI and Crypto Czar, against widespread social media backlash, labelling it as a misinformation-driven campaign. The controversy focuses on immigration fears and false allegations, detracting from pressing immigration issues while underscoring the polarized responses to Trump's cabinet picks.
title: David Sacks blasts ‘Out of control cabal’ against Sriram Krishnan

description: Clashes between forces loyal to former Syrian President Bashar Assad and rebel groups resulted in 17 deaths, including 14 security personnel. The violence erupted during an operation to arrest a former Assad regime official accused of authorizing executions. Authorities reported that the region is facing significant challenges in maintaining security post-Assad's regime.
title: 17 killed in 'ambush' by loyalists of ousted Syrian President Assad
Buy or sell: Stock recommendations by brokers for today

description: US President-elect Donald Trump humorously suggested Wayne Gretzky run for Canadian Prime Minister, dubbing him "Governor of Canada." Despite Gretzky's refusal and a backlash over his association with Trump, the tongue-in-cheek proposal reignited Trump's mockery of Canada and criticism of Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's policies.
title: Trump trolls Trudeau, touts Wayne Gretzky as Canada’s next PM
Rice shipment from India, first for Yunus government, to arrive today
‘Germany has most liberal immigration laws’

description: Despite legal issues and controversies, 'Pushpa 2' directed by Sukumar keeps strong box office momentum, amassing ₹1109.85 crore within 21 days, with ₹716.65 crore from its Hindi version. The movie faced protests and legal actions following a tragic stampede at its premiere, but the mass entertainer still significantly performs.
title: 'Pushpa 2' box office collection: Allu Arjun starrer crosses the Rs 1100 crore

description: Sam Konstas, 19, made his international debut for Australia against India, becoming the fourth-youngest Test debutant for the nation. Tensions flared with Virat Kohli during the match, highlighting the fierce rivalry. Konstas showcased his talent by scoring a maiden Test fifty off 52 balls, validating the selectors' faith in him.
title: Virat Kohli shoulders Konstas mid-pitch, gives death stare

description: A 32-year-old police constable, Vilas Mukade, shot and killed his wife and critically injured three other family members, including his two-year-old son, using his service pistol. The incident occurred at his in-laws' residence in Hingoli city amid ongoing marital disputes and discussions about divorce. Senior officers have arrested Mukade.
title: Maharashtra cop fires at kin, kills wife; son among 3 critical

description: Healthcare-focused global capability centres struggle with gender diversity, with only 28% women in the workforce, and just 15% in R&D roles. Companies like Roche, Siemens Healthineers, and Merck attribute this to mid-career attrition. Despite efforts to improve, women often hesitate to return after career breaks, influenced by social conditioning.
title: Health global capability centres grapple with unhealthy gender ratio

description: N Srinivasan resigned as vice-chairman and MD of India Cements after it became a subsidiary of UltraTech. His daughter and wife also stepped down from their roles. Srinivasan ended his 50-year association with the company, which faced financial issues recently and was acquired by Aditya Birla Group for Rs 3,954 crore.
title: India Cements' Srinivasan exits co after Birla takeover

description: Some commuters have reported higher cab fares on iPhones compared to Androids for identical rides in Chennai, raising suspicions about ride-hailing apps charging Apple users more. Experts suggest that apps may tweak fares based on device data, frequency of use, and user behavior patterns through dynamic pricing algorithms.
title: Do apps charge higher cab fares on iPhones than on Android devices?

description: Australia’s captain Pat Cummins won the toss and opted to bat in the fourth Test against India at the MCG. India fielded two spinners, with Nitish Kumar Reddy replacing Shubman Gill. The series is tied 1-1, making this Boxing Day Test crucial. Both teams made notable changes to their playing XIs.
title: IND vs AUS: Shubman Gill dropped, Sundar comes in
Christmas Day scare: Taxi hits pedestrians in Manhattan, injures many
Rupee sees relative gain as other currencies fall more vs $: RBI

description: Three years after a Gujarati family froze to death attempting to illegally cross the US-Canada border, an ED probe uncovers an international human trafficking syndicate involving Canadian colleges issuing student visas. Around 35,000 illegal migrants are sent abroad yearly by two agents in Mumbai and Nagpur.
title: 260 Canada colleges involved in trafficking: ED

description: In 2023-24, BJP garnered Rs 2,244 crore in contributions, three times more than in 2022-23, with Prudent Electoral Trust being the largest donor. Congress received Rs 288.9 crore. Electoral bond receipts were excluded as per rules.
title: BJP got Rs 2,244 crore contributions in 2023-24, Congress Rs 289 crore
